reviewText: A perfect addition to your family's collection.  These cartoons are "pre-blockbusters" (like "The Incredibles", "Tangled" & "Wreck-It Ralph") and have that charm & simplicity Walt really strived for.  Wonderful!

reviewText: Disney's Timeless Tales are just that - timeless tales. These old cartoons dating back to the 30-ties are beautifully renovated and made to look like new. I truly recommend them.

reviewText: I'm so thankful I was able to find this DVD! I was after the cartoon The Grasshopper and the Ants and here it was! It was a nice, cheap alternative to the other option of buying a boxed set. Great quality DVD! Also has the Prince and the Pauper (Mickey) and the 3 Little Pigs among others!!! A great addition to the Disney collection :-)

reviewText: ***** Five Stars for the cartoons themselves!  I give the low *** three start rating because WE ALREADY HAVE THEM ON DVD!This is a cheaply put-together re-release of shorts mostly from other DISNEY TREASURES TIN releases.1) PRINCE AND THE PAUPER (1990) also on the Micky Mouse In Living Color Volume #2 TIN DVD release. That version is widescreen, this presentation is CROPPED.2) THREE LITTLE PIGS (1933) also on the "Disney Treasures: Silly Symphonies" DVD release.3) TORTOISE AND THE HARE (1935) also on the "Disney Treasures: Silly Symphonies" DVD release.4) THE GRASSHOPPER AND THE ANTS (1934) also on the "Disney Treasures: Silly Symphonies" DVD release.5) THE PIED PIPER  (1933) also on the "Disney Treasures: Silly Symphonies volume 2" DVD release.With the TIN DVD releases on limited availability, I guess Disney hopes those who missed out will buy these 5-cartoon discs. The low price is misleading, when you break it down to individual cartoon cost this release is EXPENSIVE!And no extras!
summary: Unrestored re-release of shorts from the Disney Treasures releases.
